Why do you think Tameika
took the case?

50:45.042 --> 50:47.278
I signed a waiver so that
she could represent your mom.

50:47.311 --> 50:48.279
It was handled.

50:48.312 --> 50:49.747
So let's just get
Tameika back.

50:49.781 --> 50:50.748
I have money.

50:50.782 --> 50:52.049
It's not about money.

50:52.083 --> 50:54.519
Tameika's not gonna
suborn perjury.

50:54.552 --> 50:56.287
Your mother lied twice.

50:56.320 --> 50:58.656
First she left out
that she had an accomplice.

50:58.689 --> 51:00.625
Someone else
pulled that trigger.

51:01.692 --> 51:03.060
Damn.

51:04.562 --> 51:05.730
Do you know who it was?

51:05.763 --> 51:08.766
[scoffs]
Tasha told ADA Sullivan

51:08.800 --> 51:10.601
that Andre Coleman
killed your father.

51:10.635 --> 51:11.669
Lie number two.

51:13.104 --> 51:14.472
-Wasn't it his gun?
-It was.

51:14.505 --> 51:15.706
But we still had the clothes
he wore that night.

51:15.740 --> 51:16.808
No GSR.

51:16.841 --> 51:18.776
Andre Coleman
didn't shoot anyone

51:18.810 --> 51:20.511
20 minutes before his arrest.

51:20.545 --> 51:24.248
Even if we wanted to blame him,
now we can't.

51:27.151 --> 51:29.720
Wait, you-you-you told me
it was Dre too.

51:29.754 --> 51:31.823
That's what
my mother told me.

51:33.157 --> 51:35.193
Tariq...

51:35.226 --> 51:37.562
if you know
who your mother's protecting,

51:37.595 --> 51:38.596
you tell me.

51:40.565 --> 51:42.800
Look, man, I don't know,
a'ight?

51:42.834 --> 51:44.769
But you know my mother
didn't shoot anyone.

51:44.802 --> 51:46.571
You know she's innocent.

51:46.604 --> 51:48.139
So if you don't fix this,
I'm gonna have to tell the cops

51:48.172 --> 51:50.107
that I saw you at Truth.

51:50.141 --> 51:51.742
-I don't have a choice.
-Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

51:51.776 --> 51:54.679
You-you don't have to tell
anyone anything about me.

51:56.414 --> 51:58.216
We can still save your mom.

51:58.249 --> 51:59.784
I can still push Sullivan
to take a deal,

51:59.817 --> 52:01.752
but Tasha has to name
the shooter.

52:01.786 --> 52:03.621
If she does that
and I can confirm it,

52:03.654 --> 52:04.856
I can get her out.

52:06.557 --> 52:09.760
We can all walk away
from this, Tariq.

52:09.794 --> 52:12.697
Just get your mom
to tell the truth.

52:12.730 --> 52:15.733
♪ ♪

52:17.802 --> 52:19.403
[Brayden] Oh, yeah.

52:19.437 --> 52:21.906
Oh, yeah, just put that shit
in your ass, dog.

52:22.139 --> 52:23.174
I'm not playing
this game anymore.

52:23.207 --> 52:24.308
I quit.

52:24.342 --> 52:25.543
Yo, Zeke, I need to borrow
your phone, bro.

52:26.544 --> 52:28.379
The fuck you need
to borrow my phone for?

52:28.412 --> 52:29.447
I'm trying to make
an Instagram Live

52:29.480 --> 52:30.648
or whatever the fuck
it's called.

52:30.681 --> 52:32.216
-I don't got an account.
-Oh, dude, just use mine.

52:32.250 --> 52:33.317
You know I'm always
ready to go.

52:33.351 --> 52:34.318
Now, you know Zeke got

52:34.352 --> 52:35.620
more followers than you, bro.

52:35.653 --> 52:38.189
That's hurtful.
I'm just gonna say it.

52:38.222 --> 52:39.323
You'll be a'ight.

52:39.357 --> 52:40.558
But, yo, I need to do
something, bro.

52:40.591 --> 52:42.660
It's for my mom.

52:42.693 --> 52:45.162
[gunfire on television]

52:45.196 --> 52:47.431
I got you.

52:47.465 --> 52:48.666
Good looking, bro.

52:48.699 --> 52:50.701
[dramatic music plays]

52:50.735 --> 52:51.736
[Brayden sighs]

52:51.769 --> 52:53.838
[Tariq]
Hey, what's up, guys?

52:53.871 --> 52:55.606
I don't really do the
social media stuff like that.

52:55.640 --> 52:57.742
I don't like it,
but I need to take the time out

52:57.775 --> 52:59.443
to tell everyone
how grateful I am

52:59.477 --> 53:01.212
that the famous Davis MacLean

53:01.245 --> 53:03.514
has agreed to take
my mother's case.

53:03.548 --> 53:06.250
We're a Black family in need,
and he heard us.

53:06.284 --> 53:09.320
He showed up. Thank you.

53:11.822 --> 53:13.791
Most people look
at The Stranger as an exposure

53:13.824 --> 53:16.928
of how other people's opinions
can shape our destinies.

53:16.961 --> 53:18.729
Most people think
that if Meursault

53:18.763 --> 53:20.197
would have visibly mourned
his mother

53:20.231 --> 53:21.899
and then expressed
that emotion,

53:21.933 --> 53:23.768
then he wouldn't
have been put to death.

53:23.801 --> 53:26.337
He would've just died
by bad press.

53:26.370 --> 53:28.406
But Meursault,
he took those actions.

53:28.439 --> 53:30.508
You know, every single action
along the way was his.

53:30.541 --> 53:32.643
All those decisions were his,

53:32.677 --> 53:34.612
even the decision
to pull the trigger.

53:35.780 --> 53:38.516
Meursault, he was...
he was different.

53:39.650 --> 53:41.752
He was a killer.

53:41.786 --> 53:44.555
He was alienated.
He was special.

53:44.589 --> 53:48.626
Maybe too special to live
by everyone else's rules.

53:48.659 --> 53:51.662
Because of that difference,
he couldn't survive.

53:51.696 --> 53:52.930
But, you know,
that doesn't mean Meursault

53:52.964 --> 53:54.732
was the one who was wrong.

53:54.765 --> 53:56.701
Most people survive
by trying to live up

53:56.734 --> 53:59.670
to others' opinions
and court the public favor.

53:59.704 --> 54:02.373
You know, I think to do that is
to die while you're still here.

54:03.708 --> 54:06.377
Meursault went out
on his own terms.

54:06.410 --> 54:09.513
He didn't bend
to a prosecutor or the priest.

54:09.547 --> 54:11.582
He controlled his own destiny.

54:11.616 --> 54:14.585
[somber music plays]

54:14.619 --> 54:17.622
♪ ♪

54:20.891 --> 54:23.794
[light percussive music plays]

54:24.362 --> 54:27.331
[cell phone chiming repeatedly]

54:27.365 --> 54:30.368
♪ ♪

54:40.544 --> 54:42.847
Son of a bitch.

54:42.880 --> 54:44.682
[Tariq] Hello.

54:44.715 --> 54:46.484
[Davis]
Where do you want to meet?

54:46.517 --> 54:48.886
[Tariq] Meet me
at the chapel in 15.

54:48.919 --> 54:51.922
♪ ♪

54:58.029 --> 55:00.464
You forced my hand.

55:10.708 --> 55:11.942
This'll buy you the week,

55:11.976 --> 55:13.511
until I can find you
other counsel

55:13.544 --> 55:15.079
without attracting
public attention.

55:15.312 --> 55:16.681
All I need is the week.

55:16.714 --> 55:17.915
We official now?

55:19.917 --> 55:21.552
Yes.

55:21.585 --> 55:23.621
Can I trust you?

55:24.455 --> 55:25.823
You gotta trust someone, kid.

55:25.856 --> 55:27.825
Seems like I'm all you got.

55:30.094 --> 55:31.362
A'ight, well, the DA knows

55:31.395 --> 55:32.697
my mother didn't shoot
my father.

55:32.730 --> 55:34.465
Then why would they hit her
with a full murder charge?

55:34.498 --> 55:35.800
That doesn't make sense.

55:35.833 --> 55:37.935
'Cause she lied to them
about having an accomplice.

55:37.968 --> 55:39.737
She lied to them
about who it was.

55:40.738 --> 55:41.939
She was protecting him

55:41.972 --> 55:44.442
because he shot my father
trying to protect her.

55:44.475 --> 55:45.509
They said she could get a deal

55:45.543 --> 55:46.944
if she tells them
the whole truth.

55:46.977 --> 55:50.047
Tariq,
for a criminal defendant,

55:50.081 --> 55:51.716
the truth rarely sets you free.

55:51.749 --> 55:53.350
Doesn't matter
what the DA told her.

55:53.384 --> 55:56.353
[dramatic music plays]

55:56.387 --> 55:59.390
♪ ♪

56:00.891 --> 56:01.992
A'ight, well,
tell my mom I said

56:02.026 --> 56:04.361
that she needs to come home.

56:04.395 --> 56:05.830
A'ight,
she doesn't deserve this.

56:05.863 --> 56:08.065
She's innocent.

56:08.099 --> 56:11.102
I know she's afraid
to say his real name, but...

56:11.135 --> 56:12.837
I'm not afraid anymore.

56:14.105 --> 56:16.941
Tell my mom
I said if she loves me,

56:16.974 --> 56:19.977
then she should tell
the truth.

56:20.010 --> 56:23.013
♪ ♪

56:27.852 --> 56:30.387
[chuckles]

56:30.421 --> 56:32.056
Tariq really got you here.

56:32.089 --> 56:33.424
You raised that kid?

56:33.457 --> 56:35.025
I don't know
whether to congratulate you

56:35.059 --> 56:37.628
or have you brought up
on charges by Child Services.

56:39.497 --> 56:42.733
Okay, ADA Sullivan
is offering you

56:42.767 --> 56:44.468
the deal of the century.

56:44.502 --> 56:47.438
Obstructing governmental
administration, second degree,

56:47.471 --> 56:49.106
and tampering
with physical evidence.

56:49.140 --> 56:52.510
Three years' probation,
you allocute, you go home.

56:52.543 --> 56:54.011
[Tasha] That's the same deal
Tameika got me.

56:54.044 --> 56:55.479
Exactly.

56:55.513 --> 56:57.148
But this time, you have
to tell the whole truth.

56:57.181 --> 56:59.049
If they can't verify
your story,

56:59.083 --> 57:00.484
you go on trial for murder.

57:00.518 --> 57:01.852
It was Andre Coleman.

57:01.886 --> 57:03.554
[Davis]
It was not Andre Coleman.

57:03.587 --> 57:06.023
There was no GSR on Coleman's
clothing from that night.

57:06.056 --> 57:07.558
He's not the shooter.

57:07.591 --> 57:08.926
And you wouldn't frame
Quinton Wallace

57:08.959 --> 57:09.994
to protect Coleman.

57:11.195 --> 57:14.098
Look, you may be the first
client I've ever said this to,

57:14.131 --> 57:17.568
including my own brother,
but you need to tell the truth,

57:17.601 --> 57:21.672
right now to me
and tomorrow in court.

57:21.705 --> 57:24.675
[tense music plays]

57:24.708 --> 57:27.578
♪ ♪

57:30.848 --> 57:32.016
[Davis sighs]

57:35.119 --> 57:37.121
I saw your son
before I got here.

57:38.823 --> 57:40.057
He wanted me
to tell you something.

57:40.090 --> 57:42.526
Well, what did he say?

57:43.494 --> 57:46.964
He said you don't deserve this,
that you're innocent.

57:46.997 --> 57:48.966
He said you need to come home.

57:48.999 --> 57:52.002
♪ ♪

57:53.470 --> 57:56.974
That boy loves his mother.
I'm not surprised he said that.

57:57.007 --> 57:58.242
Oh, I wasn't either.

57:58.475 --> 58:00.578
But then he said
something else.

58:00.611 --> 58:02.012
He said he knew
that you were afraid

58:02.046 --> 58:04.748
to say the name of the person
who shot your husband,

58:04.782 --> 58:06.917
but he's not afraid
for you to say it.

58:08.219 --> 58:10.721
He said if you love him,

58:10.754 --> 58:12.556
you need to tell the truth.

58:12.590 --> 58:15.593
♪ ♪

58:16.760 --> 58:19.630
Are you sure
that's what he said?

58:19.663 --> 58:21.532
That's what he said.

58:21.565 --> 58:24.068
And you don't have a choice.

58:24.101 --> 58:27.104
♪ ♪

58:32.543 --> 58:34.211
[door clicks shut]

58:34.245 --> 58:36.814
♪ ♪

58:36.847 --> 58:37.915
[door clicks open]

58:40.718 --> 58:42.086
[door clicks shut]

58:44.688 --> 58:46.123
[bailiff]
All rise.

58:46.156 --> 58:49.059
The Honorable Judge
Janine Galanti presiding.

58:49.093 --> 58:51.562
[sighs]
Ms. Sullivan, I hear we have

58:51.595 --> 58:53.230
reached an agreement
with the defense.

58:53.264 --> 58:54.932
That's correct, Your Honor.

58:54.965 --> 58:56.934
In exchange for the name
of her accomplice,

58:56.967 --> 58:58.302
the People have agreed
to obstructing

58:58.535 --> 59:00.771
governmental administration,
second degree,

59:00.804 --> 59:02.740
and tampering
with physical evidence.

59:02.773 --> 59:04.141
Three years' probation.

59:04.174 --> 59:06.543
Ms. St. Patrick,
are you ready?

59:07.778 --> 59:09.813
Yes, Your Honor.

59:09.847 --> 59:12.316
When I was charged
with this crime,

59:12.549 --> 59:14.285
I told the police
and Ms. Sullivan

59:14.318 --> 59:18.088
that I pulled the trigger,
but that wasn't true.

59:18.122 --> 59:20.591
Someone else killed James,

59:20.624 --> 59:23.160
and they gave me the gun
to frame Quinton.

59:23.193 --> 59:27.298
He said that we would both
walk away, but he was wrong.

59:27.331 --> 59:30.935
I'm sorry, Ms. Sullivan.

59:30.968 --> 59:34.204
I was simply trying to hide
the identity of my accomplice

59:34.238 --> 59:37.608
because I was afraid,
Your Honor.

59:37.641 --> 59:40.778
I was afraid of what might
happen to my family

59:40.811 --> 59:43.814
if I told the truth.

59:43.847 --> 59:46.817
[suspenseful music plays]

59:46.850 --> 59:49.186
♪ ♪

59:49.219 --> 59:51.855
The man who killed
James St. Patrick...

59:51.889 --> 59:54.892
♪ ♪

01:00:00.331 --> 01:00:02.132
...is Tommy Egan.

01:00:02.166 --> 01:00:03.901
[people murmuring]

01:00:03.934 --> 01:00:06.804
RICO.
I told you.

01:00:06.837 --> 01:00:09.173
They silenced St. Patrick to
keep him from turning witness.

01:00:09.206 --> 01:00:11.308
What? I told you no.

01:00:11.342 --> 01:00:12.609
No.

01:00:12.643 --> 01:00:13.911
Your Honor,
may the People inquire?

01:00:13.944 --> 01:00:16.246
Your Honor, my client
held up her end of the deal.

01:00:16.280 --> 01:00:18.949
I don't know what else
the DA might need to ask.

01:00:18.983 --> 01:00:21.118
-One question.
-Proceed.

01:00:21.151 --> 01:00:24.154
I find it hard to believe
that James St. Patrick's

01:00:24.188 --> 01:00:27.391
lifelong best friend would
kill him, Mrs. St. Patrick.

01:00:27.624 --> 01:00:30.060
Why on earth would Tommy Egan
have killed your husband?

01:00:31.795 --> 01:00:34.398
-Because I asked him to.
-Your Honor, I object.

01:00:34.631 --> 01:00:36.200
-No, you're not gonna do that.
-[Galanti] Objection overruled.

01:00:36.233 --> 01:00:37.768
Queenpin.

01:00:37.801 --> 01:00:39.837
Are the People satisfied?

01:00:39.870 --> 01:00:42.940
Now, you go in there,
and you make me proud.

01:00:42.973 --> 01:00:45.175
[people murmuring]

01:00:45.209 --> 01:00:48.312
Mr. Saxe, are you addressing
the court?

01:00:48.345 --> 01:00:50.147
Uh, uh, no, Your Honor.

01:00:50.180 --> 01:00:51.315
She will.

01:00:51.348 --> 01:00:54.351
♪ ♪

01:00:58.789 --> 01:01:00.157
Sorry.

01:01:00.190 --> 01:01:02.926
♪ ♪

01:01:03.794 --> 01:01:05.796
Your Honor, the People move
to drop all charges

01:01:05.829 --> 01:01:07.698
against
Tasha Green St. Patrick.

01:01:07.731 --> 01:01:08.999
-What?
-[Davis] Your Honor, we have

01:01:09.033 --> 01:01:10.200
-an executed plea agreement.
-[Jenny] Not anymore.

01:01:10.234 --> 01:01:12.069
-[Tasha] What does she mean?
-Your Honor.

01:01:12.102 --> 01:01:15.105
♪ ♪

01:01:16.373 --> 01:01:18.242
Motion granted.

01:01:18.275 --> 01:01:20.911
I hope you know what
you're doing, Ms. Sullivan.

01:01:20.944 --> 01:01:22.413
[gavel bangs]

01:01:22.446 --> 01:01:24.248
Tasha St. Patrick,
you're under arrest

01:01:24.281 --> 01:01:26.083
for the murder
of James St. Patrick

01:01:26.116 --> 01:01:27.284
under the federal

01:01:27.317 --> 01:01:29.353
Continuing Criminal Enterprise
Kingpin Statute.

01:01:29.386 --> 01:01:30.988
Ma! No! Ma!

01:01:31.021 --> 01:01:32.056
Ma!

01:01:32.089 --> 01:01:33.824
Kingpin?
What the fuck?

01:01:33.857 --> 01:01:35.826
You know I wasn't running shit,
you motherfucker.

01:01:35.859 --> 01:01:38.028
Stay strong. We're gonna
fight this together.

01:01:39.897 --> 01:01:42.232
What kind of headline-grabbing
bullshit is this?

01:01:42.266 --> 01:01:43.934
Kingpin Statute?

01:01:43.967 --> 01:01:45.702
You're gonna give her
the needle?

01:01:45.736 --> 01:01:48.806
You and I both know
this is not a federal case.

01:01:49.840 --> 01:01:50.808
It is now.

01:01:50.841 --> 01:01:53.844
♪ ♪

01:02:02.719 --> 01:02:04.221
What don't I know
about your mother?

01:02:04.254 --> 01:02:06.490
-Hmm?
-Tariq, what have you done?

01:02:06.723 --> 01:02:08.859
Listen, I had to be the one
to do it, Ma; I had to.

01:02:08.892 --> 01:02:10.127
I'll say it was me.

01:02:10.160 --> 01:02:11.261
Take the gun out back
and dump it, all right?

01:02:11.295 --> 01:02:12.496
I know what to do.

01:02:12.729 --> 01:02:14.865
What have you just
gotten me into, kid?

01:02:16.066 --> 01:02:17.935
We take care
of each other, right?

01:02:17.968 --> 01:02:19.169
Right.

01:02:19.203 --> 01:02:21.939
I got you into the biggest
case of your career.

01:02:21.972 --> 01:02:25.375
Look, my mom is innocent.
Saxe has an agenda.

01:02:25.409 --> 01:02:27.478
The publicity
on this case is huge,

01:02:27.511 --> 01:02:29.813
and you're
right under the spotlight.

01:02:29.847 --> 01:02:33.050
Look, if you win--
when you win--

01:02:33.083 --> 01:02:34.418
we can take down Saxe
and blow up

01:02:34.451 --> 01:02:37.020
the whole entire
US Attorney's Office.

01:02:37.054 --> 01:02:38.455
Once you do that,
you'll be known

01:02:38.489 --> 01:02:42.092
as the most powerful criminal
defense attorney in New York.

01:02:42.126 --> 01:02:45.095
[exciting music plays]

01:02:45.129 --> 01:02:47.331
♪ ♪

01:02:47.364 --> 01:02:49.800
You owe me $450,000, kid.

01:02:49.833 --> 01:02:52.102
You paid for the appetizer,

01:02:52.136 --> 01:02:54.438
but we're about to get
into the full meal.

01:02:56.440 --> 01:03:00.377
♪ They made a monster
Out of me ♪

01:03:00.410 --> 01:03:04.481
♪ They put a sword
In my back ♪

01:03:04.515 --> 01:03:08.285
♪ They gave me
Till the count of three ♪

01:03:08.318 --> 01:03:10.988
♪ They set the hounds
On my tracks ♪

01:03:11.021 --> 01:03:12.556
[Meredith laughing]

01:03:12.789 --> 01:03:15.159
♪ They made a demon
Out of me ♪

01:03:15.192 --> 01:03:16.927
Welcome home, bitch.

01:03:16.960 --> 01:03:20.330
♪ Then they put a cross
To my flesh ♪

01:03:20.364 --> 01:03:24.301
♪ They put a search out
For me ♪

01:03:24.334 --> 01:03:27.905
♪ 'Cause I got some blood
On my hands ♪

01:03:27.938 --> 01:03:32.242
♪ But they won't see me
When I'm coming ♪

01:03:32.276 --> 01:03:36.113
♪ I'll be laughin'
While you're runnin', oh ♪

01:03:36.146 --> 01:03:40.150
♪ Oh, you won't see me
When I'm comin' ♪

01:03:40.184 --> 01:03:45.022
♪ I'll be that monster
You've been wantin', oh, no ♪

01:03:45.055 --> 01:03:48.058
♪ ♪

01:04:01.471 --> 01:04:05.409
♪ They made a story
Out of me ♪

01:04:05.442 --> 01:04:09.413
♪ They laugh and joke
About my name ♪

01:04:09.446 --> 01:04:13.550
♪ They put a bounty out
On me ♪

01:04:13.584 --> 01:04:16.853
♪ They're all excited
By my shame ♪

01:04:16.887 --> 01:04:21.058
♪ But they won't see me
When I'm coming ♪

01:04:21.091 --> 01:04:24.928
♪ I'll be laughin'
While you're runnin', oh ♪

01:04:24.962 --> 01:04:29.032
♪ Oh, you won't see me
When I'm comin' ♪

01:04:29.066 --> 01:04:33.503
♪ I'll be that monster
You've been wantin', oh, no ♪

01:04:33.537 --> 01:04:35.872
♪ ♪

01:04:35.906 --> 01:04:37.941
♪ Oh-ah, oh-eh ♪

01:04:37.975 --> 01:04:40.010
